I fear if we don't get the strait open in the next month or so, we will be staring down a major growth shock as these supply and demand buffers both tap out at the same time. In fact, I think it would be so bad that I view Trump crying uncle here as nearly inevitable as the consequences would be so bad otherwise.

It's like it's so bad that it's good.  

We are running out of time, but the curve of inevitable resolution is non-linear since the consequences of not resolving it would be so negative.

There's plenty of reasons to keep playing musical chair in markets and the AI trades (I still am), but just know that things must get resolved very soon here and that we're hanging by a thread.

